1. Brand Identity & EssenceBrand Name: Aeterna HorologyTagline: The Inner Truth of Time. Core Mission: To bridge the gap between industrial engineering and luxury art by making the invisible visible.PillarDescriptionPrecisionEvery micron is intentional. We celebrate the "how" as much as the "why."TransparencySkeletonized designs that hide nothing. Authenticity through exposure.MinimalismA pure, dark void that allows the complexity of the movement to be the hero.2. Visual LanguageThe Color Palette (The "Void" System)The brand exists in a high-contrast environment. The deep black background isn't just a color; it represents the infinite space in which precision exists.Primary Background: #050505 (The Void Black)Primary Accent: #D4AF37 (Galvanic Gold – representing the movement)Secondary Accent: #C0C0C0 (Brushed Steel – representing the casing)Highlight: #003366 (Heat-Blued Steel – for hands and screws)Typography: #FFFFFF (90% Opacity for headers / 60% for body)TypographyPrimary Header: Inter Tight or SF Pro Display (Bold, Tracking: -0.05em). Use for "hero" words.Sub-headers: Inter (Medium, Tracking: 0.1em, All-Caps).Body Copy: Inter (Regular, Line-height: 1.6).3. Imagery & Motion GuidelinesProduct Photography (The "Hero" Shot)Lighting: Three-point studio setup with "Rim Lighting" to define the metallic edges.Background: Must be a solid #050505. No shadows on the floor; the watch must appear to float.Focus: Ultra-sharp depth of field. Every gear tooth must be visible.The Deconstruction Aesthetic (The "Exploded" View)Logic: Components must never be scattered. They move along a vertical or longitudinal axis.Spacing: Symmetrical and mathematical.Motion: High-damping, low-stiffness springs. The movement should feel "heavy" and mechanical, not bouncy or "cartoony."4. Voice & ToneConfident: We don't need to shout. The engineering speaks for itself.Technical but Poetic: We use terms like "escapement," "tourbillon," and "torque," but we frame them as the "heartbeat" or "soul" of the machine.Exclusive: Use "we" sparingly. Focus on "The Watch" and "The Craft."Example Copy:"Twelve months of engineering. 120 individual parts. Zero secrets. Aeterna is not just a timepiece; it is a mechanical confession."5. Digital Experience (The Scroll UI)Interaction: The user "assembles" the brand through scrolling.Transitions: Fade-in-and-slide-up for text elements.Cursors: A custom, minimal circular cursor that expands when hovering over interactive mechanical parts.Sound (Optional): Subtle, high-frequency metallic "clicks" or "ticking" as the user scrolls past key gear milestones.6. Logo UsageIcon: A minimalist, geometric representation of a Balance Wheel.Wordmark: "AETERNA" in a customized sans-serif with a "stencil" cut in the letter 'A' to mimic industrial marking.Placement: Small, centered, and always white or etched gold. Never use gradients on the logo.